68#define FRAME_ID(frame) (frame.frameID().value_or(FrameIdentifier()).toUInt64())
69#define CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG(fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG(Network, "%p - CachedResource::" fmt, this, ##__VA_ARGS__)
70#define CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME(fmt, frame, ...) RELEASE_LOG(Network, "%p - [pageID=%" PRIu64 ", frameID=%" PRIu64 "] CachedResource::" fmt, this, PAGE_ID(frame), FRAME_ID(frame), ##__VA_ARGS__)

76static Seconds deadDecodedDataDeletionIntervalForResourceType(CachedResource::Type type)
77{
78 if (type == CachedResource::Type::Script)
79 return 5_s;
80
81 return MemoryCache::singleton().deadDecodedDataDeletionInterval();
82}

84DEFINE_DEBUG_ONLY_GLOBAL(WTF::RefCountedLeakCounter, cachedResourceLeakCounter, ("CachedResource"));

86CachedResource::CachedResource(CachedResourceRequest&& request, Type type, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar)
87 : m_options(request.options())
88 , m_resourceRequest(request.releaseResourceRequest())
89 , m_decodedDataDeletionTimer(*this, &CachedResource::destroyDecodedData, deadDecodedDataDeletionIntervalForResourceType(type))
90 , m_sessionID(sessionID)
91 , m_cookieJar(cookieJar)
92 , m_responseTimestamp(WallTime::now())
93 , m_fragmentIdentifierForRequest(request.releaseFragmentIdentifier())
94 , m_origin(request.releaseOrigin())
95 , m_initiatorName(request.initiatorName())
96 , m_type(type)
97 , m_preloadResult(PreloadResult::PreloadNotReferenced)
98 , m_responseTainting(ResourceResponse::Tainting::Basic)
99 , m_loadPriority(DefaultResourceLoadPriority::forResourceType(type))
100 , m_status(Pending)
101 , m_requestedFromNetworkingLayer(false)
102 , m_inCache(false)
103 , m_loading(false)
104 , m_isLinkPreload(request.isLinkPreload())
105 , m_hasUnknownEncoding(request.isLinkPreload())
106 , m_switchingClientsToRevalidatedResource(false)
107 , m_ignoreForRequestCount(request.ignoreForRequestCount())
108{
109 ASSERT(m_sessionID.isValid());
110
111 setLoadPriority(request.priority());
112#ifndef NDEBUG
113 cachedResourceLeakCounter.increment();
114#endif
115
116 // FIXME: We should have a better way of checking for Navigation loads, maybe FetchMode::Options::Navigate.
117 ASSERT(m_origin || m_type == Type::MainResource);
118
119 if (isRequestCrossOrigin(m_origin.get(), m_resourceRequest.url(), m_options))
120 setCrossOrigin();
121}

123// FIXME: For this constructor, we should probably mandate that the URL has no fragment identifier.
124CachedResource::CachedResource(const URL& url, Type type, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar)
125 : m_resourceRequest(url)
126 , m_decodedDataDeletionTimer(*this, &CachedResource::destroyDecodedData, deadDecodedDataDeletionIntervalForResourceType(type))
127 , m_sessionID(sessionID)
128 , m_cookieJar(cookieJar)
129 , m_responseTimestamp(WallTime::now())
130 , m_fragmentIdentifierForRequest(CachedResourceRequest::splitFragmentIdentifierFromRequestURL(m_resourceRequest))
131 , m_type(type)
132 , m_preloadResult(PreloadResult::PreloadNotReferenced)
133 , m_responseTainting(ResourceResponse::Tainting::Basic)
134 , m_status(Cached)
135 , m_requestedFromNetworkingLayer(false)
136 , m_inCache(false)
137 , m_loading(false)
138 , m_isLinkPreload(false)
139 , m_hasUnknownEncoding(false)
140 , m_switchingClientsToRevalidatedResource(false)
141 , m_ignoreForRequestCount(false)
142{
143 ASSERT(m_sessionID.isValid());
144#ifndef NDEBUG
145 cachedResourceLeakCounter.increment();
146#endif
147}
148
149CachedResource::~CachedResource()
150{
151 ASSERT(!m_resourceToRevalidate); // Should be true because canDelete() checks this.
152 ASSERT(canDelete());
153 ASSERT(!inCache());
154 ASSERT(!m_deleted);
155 ASSERT(url().isNull() || !allowsCaching() || MemoryCache::singleton().resourceForRequest(resourceRequest(), sessionID()) != this);
156
157#ifndef NDEBUG
158 m_deleted = true;
159 cachedResourceLeakCounter.decrement();
160#endif
161}
162
163void CachedResource::failBeforeStarting()
164{
165 // FIXME: What if resources in other frames were waiting for this revalidation?
166 LOG(ResourceLoading, "Cannot start loading '%s'", url().string().latin1().data());
167 if (allowsCaching() && m_resourceToRevalidate)
168 MemoryCache::singleton().revalidationFailed(*this);
169 error(CachedResource::LoadError);
170}
171
172void CachedResource::load(CachedResourceLoader& cachedResourceLoader)
173{
174 if (!cachedResourceLoader.frame()) {
175 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG("load: No associated frame");
176 failBeforeStarting();
177 return;
178 }
179 Frame& frame = *cachedResourceLoader.frame();
180
181 // Prevent new loads if we are in the BackForwardCache or being added to the BackForwardCache.
182 // We query the top document because new frames may be created in pagehide event handlers
183 // and their backForwardCacheState will not reflect the fact that they are about to enter page
184 // cache.
185 if (auto* topDocument = frame.mainFrame().document()) {
186 switch (topDocument->backForwardCacheState()) {
187 case Document::NotInBackForwardCache:
188 break;
189 case Document::AboutToEnterBackForwardCache:
190 // Beacons are allowed to go through in 'pagehide' event handlers.
191 if (m_options.keepAlive || shouldUsePingLoad(type()))
192 break;
193 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("load: About to enter back/forward cache", frame);
194 failBeforeStarting();
195 return;
196 case Document::InBackForwardCache:
197 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("load: Already in back/forward cache", frame);
198 failBeforeStarting();
199 return;
200 }
201 }
202
203 FrameLoader& frameLoader = frame.loader();
204 if (m_options.securityCheck == SecurityCheckPolicy::DoSecurityCheck && !m_options.keepAlive && !shouldUsePingLoad(type())) {
205 while (true) {
206 if (frameLoader.state() == FrameState::Provisional)
207 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("load: Failed security check -- state is provisional", frame);
208 else if (!frameLoader.activeDocumentLoader())
209 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("load: Failed security check -- not active document", frame);
210 else if (frameLoader.activeDocumentLoader()->isStopping())
211 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG_WITH_FRAME("load: Failed security check -- active loader is stopping", frame);
212 else
213 break;
214 failBeforeStarting();
215 return;
216 }
217 }
218
219 m_loading = true;
220
221 if (isCacheValidator()) {
222 CachedResource* resourceToRevalidate = m_resourceToRevalidate;
223 ASSERT(resourceToRevalidate->canUseCacheValidator());
224 ASSERT(resourceToRevalidate->isLoaded());
225 const String& lastModified = resourceToRevalidate->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::LastModified);
226 const String& eTag = resourceToRevalidate->response().httpHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::ETag);
227 if (!lastModified.isEmpty() || !eTag.isEmpty()) {
228 ASSERT(cachedResourceLoader.cachePolicy(type(), url()) != CachePolicy::Reload);
229 if (cachedResourceLoader.cachePolicy(type(), url()) == CachePolicy::Revalidate)
230 m_resourceRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl, HTTPHeaderValues::maxAge0());
231 if (!lastModified.isEmpty())
232 m_resourceRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfModifiedSince, lastModified);
233 if (!eTag.isEmpty())
234 m_resourceRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfNoneMatch, eTag);
235 }
236 }
237
238 if (type() == Type::LinkPrefetch)
239 m_resourceRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Purpose, "prefetch");
240 m_resourceRequest.setPriority(loadPriority());
241
242 // Navigation algorithm is setting up the request before sending it to CachedResourceLoader?CachedResource.
243 // So no need for extra fields for MainResource.
244 if (type() != Type::MainResource)
245 frameLoader.updateRequestAndAddExtraFields(m_resourceRequest, IsMainResource::No);
246
247 // FIXME: It's unfortunate that the cache layer and below get to know anything about fragment identifiers.
248 // We should look into removing the expectation of that knowledge from the platform network stacks.
249 ResourceRequest request(m_resourceRequest);
250 if (!m_fragmentIdentifierForRequest.isNull()) {
251 URL url = request.url();
252 url.setFragmentIdentifier(m_fragmentIdentifierForRequest);
253 request.setURL(url);
254 m_fragmentIdentifierForRequest = String();
255 }
256
257 if (m_options.keepAlive && type() != Type::Ping && !cachedResourceLoader.keepaliveRequestTracker().tryRegisterRequest(*this)) {
258 setResourceError({ errorDomainWebKitInternal, 0, request.url(), "Reached maximum amount of queued data of 64Kb for keepalive requests"_s, ResourceError::Type::AccessControl });
259 failBeforeStarting();
260 return;
261 }
262
263 // FIXME: Deprecate that code path.
264 if (m_options.keepAlive && shouldUsePingLoad(type()) && platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->usePingLoad()) {
265 ASSERT(m_originalRequest);
266 CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource> protectedThis(this);
267
268 unsigned long identifier = frame.page()->progress().createUniqueIdentifier();
269 InspectorInstrumentation::willSendRequestOfType(&frame, identifier, frameLoader.activeDocumentLoader(), request, InspectorInstrumentation::LoadType::Beacon);
270
271 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->startPingLoad(frame, request, m_originalRequest->httpHeaderFields(), m_options, m_options.contentSecurityPolicyImposition, [this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), protectedFrame = makeRef(frame), identifier] (const ResourceError& error, const ResourceResponse& response) {
272 if (!response.isNull())
273 InspectorInstrumentation::didReceiveResourceResponse(protectedFrame, identifier, protectedFrame->loader().activeDocumentLoader(), response, nullptr);
274 if (!error.isNull()) {
275 setResourceError(error);
276 this->error(LoadError);
277 InspectorInstrumentation::didFailLoading(protectedFrame.ptr(), protectedFrame->loader().activeDocumentLoader(), identifier, error);
278 return;
279 }
280 finishLoading(nullptr, { });
281 NetworkLoadMetrics emptyMetrics;
282 InspectorInstrumentation::didFinishLoading(protectedFrame.ptr(), protectedFrame->loader().activeDocumentLoader(), identifier, emptyMetrics, nullptr);
283 });
284 return;
285 }
286
287 platformStrategies()->loaderStrategy()->loadResource(frame, *this, WTFMove(request), m_options, [this, protectedThis = CachedResourceHandle<CachedResource>(this), frameRef = makeRef(frame)] (RefPtr<SubresourceLoader>&& loader) {
288 m_loader = WTFMove(loader);
289 if (!m_loader) {
290 RELEASE_LOG(Network, "%p - [pageID=%" PRIu64 ", frameID=%" PRIu64 "] CachedResource::load: Unable to create SubresourceLoader", this, PAGE_ID(frameRef.get()), FRAME_ID(frameRef.get()));
291 failBeforeStarting();
292 return;
293 }
294 setStatus(Pending);
295 });
296}

298void CachedResource::loadFrom(const CachedResource& resource)
299{
300 ASSERT(url() == resource.url());
301 ASSERT(type() == resource.type());
302 ASSERT(resource.status() == Status::Cached);
303
304 if (isCrossOrigin() && m_options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::Cors) {
305 ASSERT(m_origin);
306 auto accessControlCheckResult = WebCore::passesAccessControlCheck(resource.response(), m_options.storedCredentialsPolicy, *m_origin, &CrossOriginAccessControlCheckDisabler::singleton());
307 if (!accessControlCheckResult) {
308 setResourceError(ResourceError(String(), 0, url(), accessControlCheckResult.error(), ResourceError::Type::AccessControl));
309 return;
310 }
311 }
312
313 setBodyDataFrom(resource);
314 setStatus(Status::Cached);
315 setLoading(false);
316}
317
318void CachedResource::setBodyDataFrom(const CachedResource& resource)
319{
320 m_data = resource.m_data;
321 m_response = resource.m_response;
322 m_response.setTainting(m_responseTainting);
323 setDecodedSize(resource.decodedSize());
324 setEncodedSize(resource.encodedSize());
325}
326
327void CachedResource::checkNotify(const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
328{
329 if (isLoading() || stillNeedsLoad())
330 return;
331
332 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedResourceClient> walker(m_clients);
333 while (CachedResourceClient* client = walker.next())
334 client->notifyFinished(*this, metrics);
335}
336
337void CachedResource::updateBuffer(SharedBuffer&)
338{
339 ASSERT(dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::BufferData);
340}
341
342void CachedResource::updateData(const uint8_t*, unsigned)
343{
344 ASSERT(dataBufferingPolicy() == DataBufferingPolicy::DoNotBufferData);
345}
346
347void CachedResource::finishLoading(SharedBuffer*, const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
348{
349 setLoading(false);
350 checkNotify(metrics);
351}
352
353void CachedResource::error(CachedResource::Status status)
354{
355 setStatus(status);
356 ASSERT(errorOccurred());
357 m_data = nullptr;
358
359 setLoading(false);
360 checkNotify({ });
361}
362
363void CachedResource::cancelLoad()
364{
365 if (!isLoading() && !stillNeedsLoad())
366 return;
367
368 auto* documentLoader = (m_loader && m_loader->frame()) ? m_loader->frame()->loader().activeDocumentLoader() : nullptr;
369 if (m_options.keepAlive && (!documentLoader || documentLoader->isStopping()))
370 m_error = { };
371 else
372 setStatus(LoadError);
373
374 setLoading(false);
375 checkNotify({ });
376}
377
378void CachedResource::finish()
379{
380 if (!errorOccurred())
381 setStatus(Cached);
382}
383
384void CachedResource::setCrossOrigin()
385{
386 ASSERT(m_options.mode != FetchOptions::Mode::SameOrigin);
387 m_responseTainting = (m_options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::Cors) ? ResourceResponse::Tainting::Cors : ResourceResponse::Tainting::Opaque;
388}
389
390bool CachedResource::isCrossOrigin() const
391{
392 return m_responseTainting != ResourceResponse::Tainting::Basic;
393}
394
395bool CachedResource::isCORSSameOrigin() const
396{
397 // Following resource types do not use CORS
398 ASSERT(type() != Type::FontResource);
399 ASSERT(type() != Type::SVGFontResource);
400#if ENABLE(XSLT)
401 ASSERT(type() != Type::XSLStyleSheet);
402#endif
403
404 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/infrastructure.html#cors-same-origin
405 return !loadFailedOrCanceled() && m_responseTainting != ResourceResponse::Tainting::Opaque;
406}
407
408bool CachedResource::isExpired() const
409{
410 if (m_response.isNull())
411 return false;
412
413 return computeCurrentAge(m_response, m_responseTimestamp) > freshnessLifetime(m_response);
414}
415
416static inline bool shouldCacheSchemeIndefinitely(StringView scheme)
417{
418#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
419 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(scheme, "applewebdata"))
420 return true;
421#endif
422#if USE(SOUP)
423 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(scheme, "resource"))
424 return true;
425#endif
426 return equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(scheme, "data");
427}
428
429Seconds CachedResource::freshnessLifetime(const ResourceResponse& response) const
430{
431 if (!response.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily()) {
432 StringView protocol = response.url().protocol();
433 if (!shouldCacheSchemeIndefinitely(protocol)) {
434 // Don't cache non-HTTP main resources since we can't check for freshness.
435 // FIXME: We should not cache subresources either, but when we tried this
436 // it caused performance and flakiness issues in our test infrastructure.
437 if (m_type == Type::MainResource || LegacySchemeRegistry::shouldAlwaysRevalidateURLScheme(protocol.toStringWithoutCopying()))
438 return 0_us;
439 }
440
441 return Seconds::infinity();
442 }
443
444 return computeFreshnessLifetimeForHTTPFamily(response, m_responseTimestamp);
445}

447void CachedResource::redirectReceived(ResourceRequest&& request, const ResourceResponse& response, CompletionHandler<void(ResourceRequest&&)>&& completionHandler)
448{
449 CACHEDRESOURCE_RELEASE_LOG("redirectReceived:");
450
451 m_requestedFromNetworkingLayer = true;
452 if (!response.isNull())
453 updateRedirectChainStatus(m_redirectChainCacheStatus, response);
454
455 completionHandler(WTFMove(request));
456}
457
458void CachedResource::setResponse(const ResourceResponse& response)
459{
460 ASSERT(m_response.type() == ResourceResponse::Type::Default);
461 m_response = response;
462 m_varyingHeaderValues = collectVaryingRequestHeaders(cookieJar(), m_resourceRequest, m_response);
463
464#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
465 if (m_response.source() == ResourceResponse::Source::ServiceWorker) {
466 m_responseTainting = m_response.tainting();
467 return;
468 }
469#endif
470 m_response.setRedirected(m_redirectChainCacheStatus.status != RedirectChainCacheStatus::Status::NoRedirection);
471 if (m_response.tainting() == ResourceResponse::Tainting::Basic || m_response.tainting() == ResourceResponse::Tainting::Cors)
472 m_response.setTainting(m_responseTainting);
473}
474
475void CachedResource::responseReceived(const ResourceResponse& response)
476{
477 setResponse(response);
478 m_responseTimestamp = WallTime::now();
479 String encoding = response.textEncodingName();
480 if (!encoding.isNull())
481 setEncoding(encoding);
482}

484void CachedResource::clearLoader()
485{
486 if (m_loader)
487 m_identifierForLoadWithoutResourceLoader = m_loader->identifier();
488 else
489 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
490 m_loader = nullptr;
491 deleteIfPossible();
492}
493
494void CachedResource::addClient(CachedResourceClient& client)
495{
496 if (addClientToSet(client))
497 didAddClient(client);
498}
499
500void CachedResource::didAddClient(CachedResourceClient& client)
501{
502 if (m_decodedDataDeletionTimer.isActive())
503 m_decodedDataDeletionTimer.stop();
504
505 if (m_clientsAwaitingCallback.remove(&client))
506 m_clients.add(&client);
507
508 // FIXME: Make calls to notifyFinished async
509 if (!isLoading() && !stillNeedsLoad())
510 client.notifyFinished(*this, { });
511}
512
513bool CachedResource::addClientToSet(CachedResourceClient& client)
514{
515 if (m_preloadResult == PreloadResult::PreloadNotReferenced && client.shouldMarkAsReferenced()) {
516 if (isLoaded())
517 m_preloadResult = PreloadResult::PreloadReferencedWhileComplete;
518 else if (m_requestedFromNetworkingLayer)
519 m_preloadResult = PreloadResult::PreloadReferencedWhileLoading;
520 else
521 m_preloadResult = PreloadResult::PreloadReferenced;
522 }
523 if (allowsCaching() && !hasClients() && inCache())
524 MemoryCache::singleton().addToLiveResourcesSize(*this);
525
526 if ((m_type == Type::RawResource || m_type == Type::MainResource) && !m_response.isNull() && !m_proxyResource) {
527 // Certain resources (especially XHRs and main resources) do crazy things if an asynchronous load returns
528 // synchronously (e.g., scripts may not have set all the state they need to handle the load).
529 // Therefore, rather than immediately sending callbacks on a cache hit like other CachedResources,
530 // we schedule the callbacks and ensure we never finish synchronously.
531 ASSERT(!m_clientsAwaitingCallback.contains(&client));
532 m_clientsAwaitingCallback.add(&client, makeUnique<Callback>(*this, client));
533 return false;
534 }
535
536 m_clients.add(&client);
537 return true;
538}
539
540void CachedResource::removeClient(CachedResourceClient& client)
541{
542 auto callback = m_clientsAwaitingCallback.take(&client);
543 if (callback) {
544 ASSERT(!m_clients.contains(&client));
545 callback->cancel();
546 callback = nullptr;
547 } else {
548 ASSERT(m_clients.contains(&client));
549 m_clients.remove(&client);
550 didRemoveClient(client);
551 }
552
553 if (hasClients())
554 return;
555
556 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
557 if (allowsCaching() && inCache()) {
558 memoryCache.removeFromLiveResourcesSize(*this);
559 memoryCache.removeFromLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this);
560 }
561
562 if (deleteIfPossible()) {
563 // `this` object is dead here.
564 return;
565 }
566
567 if (!m_switchingClientsToRevalidatedResource)
568 allClientsRemoved();
569 destroyDecodedDataIfNeeded();
570
571 if (!allowsCaching())
572 return;
573
574 memoryCache.pruneSoon();
575}
576
577void CachedResource::allClientsRemoved()
578{
579 if (isLinkPreload() && m_loader)
580 m_loader->cancelIfNotFinishing();
581}
582
583void CachedResource::destroyDecodedDataIfNeeded()
584{
585 if (!m_decodedSize)
586 return;
587 if (!MemoryCache::singleton().deadDecodedDataDeletionInterval())
588 return;
589 m_decodedDataDeletionTimer.restart();
590}
591
592void CachedResource::decodedDataDeletionTimerFired()
593{
594 destroyDecodedData();
595}
596
597bool CachedResource::deleteIfPossible()
598{
599 if (!canDelete()) {
600 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResource %p deleteIfPossible - can't delete (hasClients %d loader %p preloadCount %u handleCount %u resourceToRevalidate %p proxyResource %p)", this, hasClients(), m_loader.get(), m_preloadCount, m_handleCount, m_resourceToRevalidate, m_proxyResource);
601 return false;
602 }
603
604 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResource %p deleteIfPossible - can delete, in cache %d", this, inCache());
605
606 if (!inCache()) {
607 deleteThis();
608 return true;
609 }
610
611 auto shouldRemoveFromCache = [&] {
612 // We may still keeps some of these cases in disk cache for history navigation.
613 if (response().cacheControlContainsNoStore())
614 return true;
615 if (isExpired() && !canUseCacheValidator())
616 return true;
617 return false;
618 }();
619
620 if (shouldRemoveFromCache) {
621 // Deletes this.
622 MemoryCache::singleton().remove(*this);
623 return true;
624 }
625
626 if (m_data)
627 m_data->hintMemoryNotNeededSoon();
628
629 return false;
630}
631
632void CachedResource::deleteThis()
633{
634 RELEASE_ASSERT(canDelete());
635 RELEASE_ASSERT(!inCache());
636
637 InspectorInstrumentation::willDestroyCachedResource(*this);
638
639 delete this;
640}
641
642void CachedResource::setDecodedSize(unsigned size)
643{
644 if (size == m_decodedSize)
645 return;
646
647 long long delta = static_cast<long long>(size) - m_decodedSize;
648
649 // The object must be moved to a different queue, since its size has been changed.
650 // Remove before updating m_decodedSize, so we find the resource in the correct LRU list.
651 if (allowsCaching() && inCache())
652 MemoryCache::singleton().removeFromLRUList(*this);
653
654 m_decodedSize = size;
655
656 if (allowsCaching() && inCache()) {
657 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
658 // Now insert into the new LRU list.
659 memoryCache.insertInLRUList(*this);
660
661 // Insert into or remove from the live decoded list if necessary.
662 // When inserting into the LiveDecodedResourcesList it is possible
663 // that the m_lastDecodedAccessTime is still zero or smaller than
664 // the m_lastDecodedAccessTime of the current list head. This is a
665 // violation of the invariant that the list is to be kept sorted
666 // by access time. The weakening of the invariant does not pose
667 // a problem. For more details please see: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=30209
668 bool inLiveDecodedResourcesList = memoryCache.inLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this);
669 if (m_decodedSize && !inLiveDecodedResourcesList && hasClients())
670 memoryCache.insertInLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this);
671 else if (!m_decodedSize && inLiveDecodedResourcesList)
672 memoryCache.removeFromLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this);
673
674 // Update the cache's size totals.
675 memoryCache.adjustSize(hasClients(), delta);
676 }
677}
678
679void CachedResource::setEncodedSize(unsigned size)
680{
681 if (size == m_encodedSize)
682 return;
683
684 long long delta = static_cast<long long>(size) - m_encodedSize;
685
686 // The object must be moved to a different queue, since its size has been changed.
687 // Remove before updating m_encodedSize, so we find the resource in the correct LRU list.
688 if (allowsCaching() && inCache())
689 MemoryCache::singleton().removeFromLRUList(*this);
690
691 m_encodedSize = size;
692
693 if (allowsCaching() && inCache()) {
694 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
695 memoryCache.insertInLRUList(*this);
696 memoryCache.adjustSize(hasClients(), delta);
697 }
698}
699
700void CachedResource::didAccessDecodedData(MonotonicTime timeStamp)
701{
702 m_lastDecodedAccessTime = timeStamp;
703
704 if (allowsCaching() && inCache()) {
705 auto& memoryCache = MemoryCache::singleton();
706 if (memoryCache.inLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this)) {
707 memoryCache.removeFromLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this);
708 memoryCache.insertInLiveDecodedResourcesList(*this);
709 }
710 memoryCache.pruneSoon();
711 }
712}
713
714void CachedResource::setResourceToRevalidate(CachedResource* resource)
715{
716 ASSERT(resource);
717 ASSERT(!m_resourceToRevalidate);
718 ASSERT(resource != this);
719 ASSERT(m_handlesToRevalidate.isEmpty());
720 ASSERT(resource->type() == type());
721 ASSERT(!resource->m_proxyResource);
722
723 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResource %p setResourceToRevalidate %p", this, resource);
724
725 resource->m_proxyResource = this;
726 m_resourceToRevalidate = resource;
727}
728
729void CachedResource::clearResourceToRevalidate()
730{
731 ASSERT(m_resourceToRevalidate);
732 ASSERT(m_resourceToRevalidate->m_proxyResource == this);
733
734 if (m_switchingClientsToRevalidatedResource)
735 return;
736
737 m_resourceToRevalidate->m_proxyResource = nullptr;
738 m_resourceToRevalidate->deleteIfPossible();
739
740 m_handlesToRevalidate.clear();
741 m_resourceToRevalidate = nullptr;
742 deleteIfPossible();
743}
744
745void CachedResource::switchClientsToRevalidatedResource()
746{
747 ASSERT(m_resourceToRevalidate);
748 ASSERT(m_resourceToRevalidate->inCache());
749 ASSERT(!inCache());
750
751 LOG(ResourceLoading, "CachedResource %p switchClientsToRevalidatedResource %p", this, m_resourceToRevalidate);
752
753 m_switchingClientsToRevalidatedResource = true;
754 for (auto& handle : m_handlesToRevalidate) {
755 handle->m_resource = m_resourceToRevalidate;
756 m_resourceToRevalidate->registerHandle(handle);
757 --m_handleCount;
758 }
759 ASSERT(!m_handleCount);
760 m_handlesToRevalidate.clear();
761
762 Vector<CachedResourceClient*> clientsToMove;
763 for (auto& entry : m_clients) {
764 CachedResourceClient* client = entry.key;
765 unsigned count = entry.value;
766 while (count) {
767 clientsToMove.append(client);
768 --count;
769 }
770 }
771
772 for (auto& client : clientsToMove)
773 removeClient(*client);
774 ASSERT(m_clients.isEmpty());
775
776 for (auto& client : clientsToMove)
777 m_resourceToRevalidate->addClientToSet(*client);
778 for (auto& client : clientsToMove) {
779 // Calling didAddClient may do anything, including trying to cancel revalidation.
780 // Assert that it didn't succeed.
781 ASSERT(m_resourceToRevalidate);
782 // Calling didAddClient for a client may end up removing another client. In that case it won't be in the set anymore.
783 if (m_resourceToRevalidate->m_clients.contains(client))
784 m_resourceToRevalidate->didAddClient(*client);
785 }
786 m_switchingClientsToRevalidatedResource = false;
787}
788
789void CachedResource::updateResponseAfterRevalidation(const ResourceResponse& validatingResponse)
790{
791 m_responseTimestamp = WallTime::now();
792
793 updateResponseHeadersAfterRevalidation(m_response, validatingResponse);
794}
795
796void CachedResource::registerHandle(CachedResourceHandleBase* h)
797{
798 ++m_handleCount;
799 if (m_resourceToRevalidate)
800 m_handlesToRevalidate.add(h);
801}
802
803void CachedResource::unregisterHandle(CachedResourceHandleBase* h)
804{
805 ASSERT(m_handleCount > 0);
806 --m_handleCount;
807
808 if (m_resourceToRevalidate)
809 m_handlesToRevalidate.remove(h);
810
811 if (!m_handleCount)
812 deleteIfPossible();
813}

815bool CachedResource::canUseCacheValidator() const
816{
817 if (m_loading || errorOccurred())
818 return false;
819
820 if (m_response.cacheControlContainsNoStore())
821 return false;
822 // Network process will handle revalidation for s-w-r.
823 if (m_response.cacheControlStaleWhileRevalidate())
824 return false;
825 return m_response.hasCacheValidatorFields();
826}
827
828CachedResource::RevalidationDecision CachedResource::makeRevalidationDecision(CachePolicy cachePolicy) const
829{
830 switch (cachePolicy) {
831 case CachePolicy::HistoryBuffer:
832 return RevalidationDecision::No;
833
834 case CachePolicy::Reload:
835 return RevalidationDecision::YesDueToCachePolicy;
836
837 case CachePolicy::Revalidate:
838 if (m_response.cacheControlContainsImmutable() && m_response.url().protocolIs("https")) {
839 if (isExpired())
840 return RevalidationDecision::YesDueToExpired;
841 return RevalidationDecision::No;
842 }
843 return RevalidationDecision::YesDueToCachePolicy;
844
845 case CachePolicy::Verify:
846 if (m_response.cacheControlContainsNoCache())
847 return RevalidationDecision::YesDueToNoCache;
848 // FIXME: Cache-Control:no-store should prevent storing, not reuse.
849 if (m_response.cacheControlContainsNoStore())
850 return RevalidationDecision::YesDueToNoStore;
851
852 if (isExpired())
853 return RevalidationDecision::YesDueToExpired;
854
855 return RevalidationDecision::No;
856 };
857 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
858 return RevalidationDecision::No;
859}

861bool CachedResource::redirectChainAllowsReuse(ReuseExpiredRedirectionOrNot reuseExpiredRedirection) const

874unsigned CachedResource::overheadSize() const
875{
876 static const int kAverageClientsHashMapSize = 384;
877 return sizeof(CachedResource) + m_response.memoryUsage() + kAverageClientsHashMapSize + m_resourceRequest.url().string().length() * 2;
878}

888inline CachedResource::Callback::Callback(CachedResource& resource, CachedResourceClient& client)
889 : m_resource(resource)
890 , m_client(client)
891 , m_timer(*this, &Callback::timerFired)
892{
893 m_timer.startOneShot(0_s);
894}
895
896inline void CachedResource::Callback::cancel()
897{
898 if (m_timer.isActive())
899 m_timer.stop();
900}

902void CachedResource::Callback::timerFired()
903{
904 m_resource.didAddClient(m_client);
905}

907#if ENABLE(SHAREABLE_RESOURCE)
908
909void CachedResource::tryReplaceEncodedData(SharedBuffer& newBuffer)
910{
911 if (!m_data)
912 return;
913
914 if (!mayTryReplaceEncodedData())
915 return;
916
917 // We have to compare the buffers because we can't tell if the replacement file backed data is for the
918 // same resource or if we made a second request with the same URL which gave us a different resource.
919 // We have seen this happen for cached POST resources.
920 if (*m_data != newBuffer)
921 return;
922
923 m_data->clear();
924 m_data->append(newBuffer);
925 didReplaceSharedBufferContents();
926}

928#endif
